]<br>[[Thomas Rhett]]<br>[[Aaron Lewis (musician)|Aaron Lewis]]<br>[[A Thousand Horses]] || rowspan=2|\u2014 || rowspan=2|Buckeye Country Superfest || rowspan=2|\u2014 || rowspan=2|\u2014 || rowspan=2|\n|-\n| June 19, 2016 || [[Luke Bryan]]<br>[[Florida Georgia Line]]<br>[[Dierks Bentley]]<br>[[Randy Houser]]<br>[[Jerrod Niemann]]<br>[[The Swon Brothers]]  \n|-\n| July 7, 2018 || [[Taylor Swift]] || [[Camila Cabello]]<br>[[Charli XCX]] || [[Taylor Swift's Reputation Stadium Tour]] || 62,897 / 62,897 || $6,606,529 || First woman to headline a concert at the stadium. \n|-\n| August 16, 2018 || [[Beyonc\u00e9]]<br>[[Jay-Z]] || [[Chloe X Halle]] and [[DJ Khaled]] || [[On the Run II Tour]] || 35,083 / 35,083 || $3,142,160 || \n|}\n\n===High school===\nThe stadium hosted the [[Ohio High School Athletic Association]] football championship games for all seven divisions in 2014 and 2015.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/sports/2010/07/22/ohsaa-fb-7-22-art-gla98ik7-1.html| last=Znidar| first=Mark| title=Football finals are coming back to the 'Shoe| website=Columbus Dispatch| date=July 22, 2010| accessdate=September 21, 2014| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150427143219/http://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/sports/2010/07/22/ohsaa-fb-7-22-art-gla98ik7-1.html| archive-date=April 27, 2015| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> The stadium had previously hosted the championships for Divisions I and III in 1982 and all divisions (five at the time) from 1983 to 1989.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable  collapsible collapsed\"\n|-\n! colspan=8|OHSAA Football State Championship Games Played at Ohio Stadium<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ohsaa.org/sports/history/ft/state_results.htm|title=All-Time State Tournament Results|website=OHSAA.org|accessdate=September 21, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150113091301/http://ohsaa.org/sports/history/FT/state_results.htm|archive-date=January 13, 2015|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n! Year !! Divisi