|Guarnieri]] (16)\n|stadium = [[Arena Civica]]\n\n|leftarm1 = 0050E0\n|pattern_la1 = _inter2930h\n|pattern_b1 = _inter3940h\n|pattern_ra1 = _inter2930h\n|body1 = 0050E0\n|rightarm1 = 0050E0\n|shorts1 = 000000\n|socks1 = 000000\n|pattern_so1 =\n\n|prevseason = [[1938\u201339 A.S. Ambrosiana-Inter season |1938-39]]\n|nextseason = [[1940\u201341 A.S. Ambrosiana-Inter season |1940-41]]\n}}\nThe 1939-40 season was Associazione Sportiva Ambrosiana-Inter's 31st in existence and 24th consecutive season in the top flight of Italian football.\n\n== Summary ==\nThe club  clinched the title, fifth in its history<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2002/febbraio/09/chi_giocatore_che_vinto_piu_sw_0_020209547.shtml|title=Chi \u00e8 il giocatore che ha vinto pi\u00f9 Scudetti ?|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|date=9 February 2002}}</ref>, and third as Ambrosiana<ref>{{cita web|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,3/articleid,0030_01_1939_0221A_0003_24257497/|title=L'Ambrosiana ha meritato la vittoria ma la Juventus ha ragione di dire che 4 a 0 sono troppi|publisher=La Stampa|date=18 September 1939|p=3}}</ref>, in [[Coppa Italia]] lost against [[Torino F.C.|Torino]], in [[Mitropa Cup]] the squad is defeated by [[\u00dajpest FC|\u00dajpest]] and its manager Bella Guttmann. Injured on the left foot [[Giuseppe Meazza|Meazza]] stood in bench almost the entire season<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2010/agosto/23/mito_Meazza_nato_cent_anni_ga_10_100823102.shtml|title=Il mito di Meazza \u00e8 nato cent'anni fa|author=Germano Bovolenta|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|date=23 August 2010}}</ref>. The nerazzurri on the top of the table with [[Tony Cargnelli]] as manager, defeating [[Bologna Football Club 1909|Bologna]] in the final round and enjoyed the title in [[Stadio Giuseppe Meazza|San Siro]], field of rival [[Associazione Calcio Milan|Milan]], due to attendance was bigger than [[Arena Civica]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enciclopediadelcalcio.it/Inter3.html|title=I brillanti anni '30 - I trionfi della seconda parte degli anni '30|publisher=enciclopediadelcalcio.it}}</ref>\n\n== Squad ==\n{{fs start}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Angelo Caimo]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giuseppe Peruchetti]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giuseppe Ballerio]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Celso Battaia]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Carmelo Buonocore]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Ugo Locatelli]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Bernardo Poli]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Duilio Setti]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Aldo Campatelli]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Enrico Candiani]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Antonio Caracciolo]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Attilio Demar\u00eda]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs mid}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Ferrari]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Ezio Meneghello]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Renato Olmi]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ARG|name=[[V\u00edctor Pozzo]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giorgio Barsanti]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Pietro Ferraris]]|pos=FW}}II\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Annibale Frossi]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Umberto Guarnieri]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giuseppe Meazza]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Pietro Rebuzzi]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Vittorio Rovelli]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs end}}\n\n== Competitions ==\n=== Serie A ===\n{{main|1939\u201340 Serie A}}\n==== League table====\n{{:1939\u201340 Serie A|showteam=AMB}}\n\n==== Matches ====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 17 September 1939\n|round=1\n|team1 = Ambrosiana-Inter\n|team2 = [[Juventus]]\n|score = 4-0\n|report =http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1939/2731/\n|location = [[Milano]]\n|sta