son]]\n\n=== Elections in the 1930s ===\n{{Election box begin|title=[[1935 United Kingdom general election|General election 1935]]: Yeovil<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">F W S Craig, British Parliamentary Election Results 1918-1949; Political Reference Publications, Glasgow 1949</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |candidate  =  [[George Davies (politician)|George Davies]]\n  |votes      = 17,640\n  |percentage = 46.8\n  |change     = -4.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = James Douglas Bateman\n  |votes      = 12,482\n  |percentage = 33.1\n  |change     = -2.4\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Albert Edward Millett\n  |votes      = 7,567\n  |percentage = 20.1\n  |change     = +6.5\n}}\n{{Election box majority\n  |votes      = 5,158\n  |percentage = 13.7\n  |change     = -1.7\n}}\n{{Election box turnout\n  |votes      = \n  |percentage = 78.3\n  |change     = -5.8\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link\n  |winner     = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |swing      = -0.9\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n[[File:Hamilton Fyfe.jpg|thumb|120px|Hamilton Fyfe]]\n{{Election box begin|title=[[1931 United Kingdom general election|General election 1931]]: Yeovil<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |candidate  =  [[George Davies (politician)|George Davies]]\n  |votes      = 20,165\n  |percentage = 50.9\n  |change     = +9.8\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Percy Holt Heffer\n  |votes      = 14,046\n  |percentage = 35.5\n  |change     = -3.3\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[Hamilton Fyfe]]\n  |votes      = 5,377\n  |percentage = 13.6\n  |change     = -6.5\n}}\n{{Election box majority\n  |votes      = 